Your menstrual cycle is more than a monthly inconvenience. It is one of the most detailed health reports your body produces every single month.

## What a healthy cycle looks like

A typical cycle runs between 21 and 35 days. Flow lasts 2 to 7 days. Pain should be manageable — not debilitating.

## When to pay attention

Changes in your cycle — irregular timing, unusually heavy flow, severe cramping — are worth discussing with a doctor. They can be early signals of conditions like PCOS, endometriosis, or thyroid issues.

## The takeaway

Your body is always communicating. Learning to listen is one of the most powerful things you can do for your long-term health.
